The paper deals with the concept of computational complexity and the difficulty of computing certain functions. This is a central topic in computer science and falls under the category of computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the concept of approximation of Turing machines, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of partitioning and equivalence relations is a common technique in discrete mathematics and logic (cs.LO). The paper also touches on the properties of computable functions, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL).
